---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';

const post = postBySlug('airbnb-handyman-ka-postcodes')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/ayrshire-bathroom-oak-door-swap-10-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: post.author,
    worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  articleSection: 'Short-let & Airbnb maintenance',
  keywords: [post.keyword, 'short let maintenance KA1', 'holiday let repairs Kilmarnock', 'Airbnb turnover handyman', 'short-let co-host maintenance'],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
  about: [{ '@type': 'Place', name: 'Ayrshire, Scotland' }],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="article"
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        Short-let owners have a specific kind of nightmare — the shower's
        broken, check-in is in three hours, and the cleaner's already gone.
        This is how we run turnover cover for Airbnb and holiday-let hosts
        across the KA postcodes, keyless-access set-ups and all.
      </p>
    </header>
    <BlogHero slug="ayrshire-bathroom-oak-door-swap-10" />


    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <p>
        Short-let work is a steady part of our week. We cover Airbnbs and
        holiday lets from the seafront flats in
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/ayr/`}>Ayr</a> and
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/troon/`}>Troon</a> through to the golf-let
        cottages near Royal Troon, townhouses in
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/kilmarnock/`}>Kilmarnock</a>, and a handful
        of stone cottages near Culzean and
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/maybole/`}>Maybole</a>. The hosts are often
        remote — Edinburgh, Glasgow, London, sometimes overseas — and they
        need someone local who can pick up the phone at a stupid hour,
        deal with a problem without supervision, and send a proper invoice
        after.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is how we run that.
      </p>

      <h2>Same-day response for between-guest problems</h2>
      <p>
        The characteristic short-let call is: last guest checked out at 10am,
        cleaner flagged something, next guest arrives at 4pm, host is three
        hours away. We have done enough of these to know the usual suspects:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Shower broken</strong> — most often a snapped hose, a
          calcium-clogged head, or a failed thermostatic cartridge. Hose and
          head we swap in 20 minutes; cartridge we carry universal spares
          for the common Mira and Triton models. See our guide on
          <a href={`${BASE}/blog/electric-shower-replacement-cumnock/`}>electric
          shower replacement</a> for the deeper version.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Blocked drain or toilet</strong> — rods, plunger and
          wet-vac in the van. 90% of the time we clear it inside the hour.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Bust blinds or curtain track</strong> — we carry spare
          mechanisms for the common roller and venetian sizes. Replace or
          rehang on site.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>TV or router not working</strong> — we do the obvious
          power-cycle, re-cable, log back in. Not IT specialists but we can
          get 95% of short-let AV faults working again.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Broken handles, locks, internal doors</strong> — Fraser's
          daily bread. Universal handles in the van.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Heating or hot-water fault</strong> — non-gas parts we
          handle (timer, thermostat, pump). Gas we do not touch — we'll
          ring a gas-registered engineer for you and stay on site until they
          arrive if you want.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We aim for a two-hour arrival window on genuine short-let
        emergencies across the KA postcodes during daylight. Earlier if
        we happen to already be in the area (often we are — we work across
        these postcodes every day).
      </p>

            <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <BlogFigure slug="ayrshire-bath-reseal-04" />
      </div>

      <h2>Keyless access or agent collection</h2>
      <p>
        Short-let owners tend to already have one of three access systems
        in place. We work with all of them:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Keysafe or keybox</strong> — you send us the code on
          WhatsApp, we log the in/out time, we rotate the code after the
          visit if you ask us to (we will not change it without your say-so).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Smart lock</strong> (Yale Keyless, August, Nuki and
          similar) — you generate a one-time code, we use it, it expires.
          Clean audit trail.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cleaner or co-host key handover</strong> — we collect the
          key from your cleaner or co-host, do the job, return it. Works
          well in Ayr and Troon where there is usually a local hand.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We <strong>never</strong> keep keys to a short-let unless you
        specifically ask us to, and if we do we label them by postcode
        alone — never the full address — and store them in a lockbox at
        the yard. Standard property-management hygiene.
      </p>

      <h2>Itemised invoice for Airbnb reimbursement</h2>
      <p>
        If the damage was caused by the previous guest and you want to
        claim it back through Airbnb's AirCover or a direct security-deposit
        deduction, the invoice shape matters. Our short-let invoices
        always include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Date and time of the visit.</li>
        <li>Full address.</li>
        <li>
          Scope of works in plain English — "replace snapped shower hose,
          test shower at normal pressure for 10 minutes" rather than
          "bathroom".
        </li>
        <li>Labour line and materials line, split.</li>
        <li>Before and after photos attached.</li>
        <li>Our ABN — well, our trading name, address and phone.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        That format has got our hosts reimbursement on AirCover claims
        repeatedly. We are not guaranteeing anything — AirCover decisions
        are Airbnb's — but clean invoices help.
      </p>

      <h2>Repeat-customer setup</h2>
      <p>
        If you own or manage more than one short-let in the KA postcodes,
        we run a repeat-customer setup. What that looks like in practice:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>No short-let surcharge</strong> — we do not charge extra
          for holiday-let properties over residential.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Priority slots for regulars</strong> on small jobs (hose
          swap, blind re-fit, silicone redo). Every job priced individually.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Consolidated monthly invoice</strong> for three or more
          properties, 30-day payment terms.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Winter-prep visit</strong> — we run a pre-season check
          for regulars in October: gutter clear, fence check, silicones,
          showers flushed, heating tested. Better value as a package than
          called in separately. More detail on our
          <a href={`${BASE}/services/property-maintenance/`}>property
          maintenance</a> page.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For the full contractor-type setup — regular cover, priority slots,
        monthly billing — drop us a message and we will put together a
        bespoke scope. We do not do minimum-contract lock-ins.
      </p>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <h3>Do you answer calls outside office hours?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. Fraser picks up the phone and Aidan runs the WhatsApp.
        Out-of-hours calls (10pm–6am) are priced individually — phone
        or WhatsApp for a free no-obligation quote.
      </p>
      <h3>Do you handle gas boilers?</h3>
      <p>
        No — we do not do gas work. We will isolate the appliance, make the
        property safe, and coordinate a gas-registered engineer on your
        behalf if you want.
      </p>
      <h3>Do you cover Airbnbs in Ayr, Troon and Prestwick?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. <a href={`${BASE}/areas/ayr/`}>Ayr</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/troon/`}>Troon</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/prestwick/`}>Prestwick</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/irvine/`}>Irvine</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/maybole/`}>Maybole</a>, Kilmarnock, Cumnock,
        Mauchline and the rest of our 10-mile patch with no surcharge.
        Outside that radius we will still come, there is a small travel
        add-on.
      </p>
      <h3>Can you send photos during the visit?</h3>
      <p>
        Standard. We WhatsApp you a before-shot when we arrive, a
        work-in-progress if there is anything you need to approve, and an
        after-shot when we leave. Hosts tell us it is the bit that matters
        most — you can see the problem is genuinely fixed.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />

  <CTABlock
    heading="Guest-gap emergency? We'll cover it."
    sub="Send Aidan the postcode and a photo. We'll tell you straight whether we can be on-site before the next check-in."
    location="Ayrshire"
  />
</BaseLayout>
